        "goseg/config/version.go:17-20 defines mutable globals (`VersionServerReady`, `VersionInfo`) and `CheckVersion` mutates/returns them as implicit shared state (lines 46-47, 77, 94-95)."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Introduce explicit state owners with interfaces (e.g., `StartramStore`, `VersionStore`) and inject them into call sites; replace package-global mutable variables with encapsulated structs guarded by synchronization where needed.",
      "confidence": "high",
      "impact_scope": "subsystem",
      "fix_scope": "architectural_change",
      "root_cause_cluster": "implicit_global_orchestration"
    },
    {
      "dimension": "cross_module_architecture",
      "identifier": "transport_domain_persistence_mixed_in_single_modules",
      "summary": "Network transport logic is tightly mixed with config persistence and event emission, collapsing module boundaries.",
      "related_files": [
        "goseg/startram/startram.go",
        "goseg/config/version.go",
        "goseg/handler/upload.go"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "goseg/startram/startram.go `Retrieve` performs HTTP, decodes payload, mutates config state (`config.UpdateConf` at lines 107-109), and emits module event (`EventBus <- ...` at line 117) in one flow.",
        "goseg/config/version.go `CheckVersion` performs HTTP polling and also writes a persisted JSON snapshot to disk (`os.Create` line 80, encoder writes lines 88-90).",
        "goseg/handler/upload.go delegates directly to importer session mutation (`importer.SetUploadSession`, `importer.Reset`) from websocket action dispatch, without an intermediate application service boundary."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Split responsibilities into explicit layers: API client layer for HTTP calls, domain service layer for registration/version workflows, and persistence/event adapters; handlers should call service interfaces, not storage/session primitives directly.",
      "confidence": "high",
      "impact_scope": "subsystem",
      "fix_scope": "architectural_change",
      "root_cause_cluster": "implicit_global_orchestration"
    },
    {
      "dimension": "cross_module_architecture",
      "identifier": "bidirectional_config_startram_dependency_drift",
      "summary": "Startram and config modules are mutually entangled through reads and writes, weakening dependency direction.",
      "related_files": [
        "goseg/startram/startram.go",
        "goseg/config/version.go"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "goseg/startram/startram.go depends on config for runtime reads (`config.Conf()` throughout) and writes (`config.UpdateConf`, `config.StartramConfig` mutation).",
        "goseg/config/version.go maintains its own remote-fetch orchestration and global status state rather than depending on a dedicated outbound service abstraction, reinforcing horizontal coupling between runtime config and external API concerns."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Define a narrow configuration interface consumed by startram (read/update methods only) and move external API orchestration into dedicated service packages so config remains a state provider instead of a peer orchestrator.",
      "confidence": "medium",
